Cascading Style Sheets

css zen garden - see site

Specificty says that each rule has a certain specificity score. Higher is what's applied.
Inline styles are more specific; not as good to use due to diff in later edits.
Higher number of selectors wins like body > h1 vs h1

important has specificity of infinity.
inline has specificity of 1000
ID have specificity of 100
class has specificity of 10
tag has " of 1


Three ways to do styles: inline, in <style></style>, and in stylesheet.
If multiple <link> tags are included in index.html, the one they are processed in order and lowest on page will override ones above.
